            "en-x-generated": "<p>To be recognised as an EIA expert, you must meet:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> which apply to all environmental recognitions<ul><li>in the 3 years preceding the application for the Flemish certificate of recognition, the applicant has not received a criminal conviction in a <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">member state of the European Economic Area</a> for breaches of environmental legislation relating to the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years preceding the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special conditions of recognition:</strong><ul><li>be a natural person.</li><li>have at least a <strong>bachelor'</strong> s degree or an equivalent degree and<ul><li>have at least <strong>5 years' experience</strong> per requested sub-domain in collaborating in the preparation of environmental impact studies (in a period of 7 years prior to the application for recognition)</li></ul></li><li>or you must have at least a <strong>master's</strong> degree or equivalent and<ul><li>have at least <strong>3 years' experience</strong> in collaborating in the preparation of environmental impact studies per requested sub-domain (within a period of 5 years prior to the application for recognition)</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>have passed a 60-hour training course</strong> covering the subjects stipulated in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36635&amp;woLang=nl\">Annex 9 of the VLAREL</a>. The subjects differ depending on the discipline or sub-domain</p></li><li><p>if you apply for accreditation as an EIR expert for the Noise or Vibration sub-domain, you must hold accreditation as an <strong>environmental expert in the discipline 'Noise and vibrations'</strong> for the Noise or Vibration sub-domain.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3>Disciplines and sub-domains</h3><p>You can apply for accreditation as an EIA expert for various <strong>disciplines</strong> and <strong>sub-domains:</strong></p><div data-table><table data-table-type=\"grid\"><thead><tr><th>Discipline</th><th>Sub-domain</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>biodiversity</td><td>no sub-domains</td></tr><tr><td>soil</td><td><ul><li>geology</li><li>pedology</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>noise and vibrations</td><td><ul><li>noise</li><li>vibrations</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>climate</td><td>no sub-domains</td></tr><tr><td>landscape, built heritage and archaeology</td><td><ul><li>landscape</li><li>architectural heritage</li><li>archaeology</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>air</td><td><ul><li>air pollution </li><li>odour</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>man</td><td><ul><li>spatial aspects</li><li>mobility</li><li>health</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>water</td><td><ul><li>surface and wastewater</li><li>geohydrology</li><li>marine waters</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table></div>",
